<h2 id="delivery-of-documents-by-post">Delivery of documents by post</h2>

<p>Anyone filing documents at Companies House should <a href="#duty-guide">understand their legal responsibilities</a>.</p>

<p>Accounts must be delivered to Companies House by their due date. If accounts are filed late, the company will be issued with a late filing penalty.</p>

<p>You can <a rel="external" href="https://beta.companieshouse.gov.uk/">check your company record</a> to see when your due dates for filing are and that details held at Companies House are up to date.</p>

<p>The Registrar of Companies cannot accept delays in transit as a reason to waive a penalty.</p>

<p>Company names on documents need to be given in full eg A Demo Company Limited shouldn’t abbreviate their name to A Demo Co Ltd. Abbreviations in company names aren’t acceptable.</p>

<p>All documents must be <a href="#reg-powers">delivered to the Registrar in an acceptable format</a> or they will be returned to the presenter or the company for amendment.</p>

<h3 id="using-a-postal-delivery-service">Using a postal delivery service</h3>

<p>If you’re using a postal delivery service we suggest that you:</p>

<ul>
  <li>be aware that <a href="#royal-mail">postal and other delivery services</a> may be subject to loss or delay</li>
  <li>note any industrial disputes or other factors which may make it difficult for a carrier to deliver on time</li>
  <li>use a guaranteed delivery service when posting close to a deadline</li>
</ul>

<div class="address"><div class="adr org fn"><p>

We will acknowledge receipt of documents if you provide a stamped addressed envelope and a copy of your covering letter - this only confirms we've received the document, not that it has been registered.
<br></br>
</p></div></div>

<h3 id="where-to-send-your-documents">Where to send your documents</h3>

<p>English and Welsh companies must send their documents to the <a href="#cdf-addrs">registrar in Cardiff</a>.</p>

<p>Scottish companies must send their documents to the <a href="#edn-addrs">registrar in Edinburgh</a>.</p>

<p>Northern Ireland companies must send their documents to the <a href="#belf-addrs">registrar in Belfast</a>.</p>

<h3 id="additional-information">Additional information</h3>

<p id="duty-guide">Guidance on the legal responsibilities of company directors, the due dates for filing accounts and the delivery of documents to the Registrar of Companies can be found in our <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/companies-house-guidance-for-limited-companies-partnerships-and-other-company-types">guidance</a>.</p>

<p id="reg-powers">More detailed information on what is considered the proper delivery of a document can be found in our guide on the <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/company-registrars-rules-and-powers">Registrar’s rules and powers</a>.</p>

<p id="royal-mail">Royal Mail’s quality of service report (March to September 2018) shows that more than 7% of first class mail may not be delivered by the next working day after posting.</p>
</div>
